    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Boil</strong> a kettle</p> <p><strong>Peel</strong> the onion<span class=\"text-danger\">(s)</span>&nbsp;and chop coarsely</p> <p><strong>Peel</strong> the garlic and chop coarsely&nbsp;</p> <p><strong>Peel</strong> the ginger (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and chop coarsely</p> <p>&nbsp;</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/norman-musas-malay-chicken-curry/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Add</strong> the rice, 350ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> (700ml)</span> water and salt (optional) to a pot with a lid over a high heat and bring to the boil</p> <p><strong>Once</strong> boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p> <p><strong>Once</strong> cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/norman-musas-malay-chicken-curry/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, place the coconut cream sachet<span class=\"text-danger\">(s)</span> in a mug and cover with boiled water until fully submerged (this softens the naturally hard cream)</p> <p><strong>Blitz</strong> the onion, garlic and ginger in a food processor (or with a hand blender) until fine</p> <p><strong>Heat</strong> a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium heat with 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> (4 tbsp)</span> vegetable oil</p> <p>&nbsp;</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/norman-musas-malay-chicken-curry/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Add</strong> the blitzed ingredients and cook until softened and lightly golden brown (approx. 3-4 min), then add the star anise, cinnamon and bay leaves and cook for a further 30 seconds&nbsp;</p> <p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, mix the curry powder with 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">(200ml)</span> water in a bowl</p> <p>Tip: Diluting the curry powder prevents it from clumping up whilst frying!</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/norman-musas-malay-chicken-curry/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Add</strong> the curry powder mixture, tamarind paste and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">(2 tsp)</span> salt (fine sea salt preferably) to the pan and cook for 2-3 min, stirring often to prevent sticking to the bottom</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/norman-musas-malay-chicken-curry/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Add</strong> the chicken, 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">(200ml)</span> boiled water and the softened coconut cream and reduce the heat to low</p> <p><strong>Cook</strong> until the chicken is cooked through (approx. 7-10 min) and the sauce has thickened</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/norman-musas-malay-chicken-curry/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, chop the coriander finely, including the stalks&nbsp;</p> <p><strong>Fluff</strong> the cooked rice with a fork</p> <p><span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>Once</strong> the chicken is cooked, add 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">(2 tsp)</span> sugar and taste, you may want to add more if needed</span></p> <p>Tip: The sugar helps temper the sourness from the tamarind!</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/norman-musas-malay-chicken-curry/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Discard</strong> the bay leaves and star anise</p> <p><strong>Stir</strong> most of the coriander through the rice, scoop the curry out into bowls and serve with rice</p> <p><span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>Garnish</strong> with the remaining coriander and enjoy!</span></p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
